////subiendo al server heroku /////

1: copiar los archivos package-lock.json y package.json  a la carpeta ./dist

2:  cambiar la ruta de inicio del server en package.json a:  "node index.js"


Install the Heroku CLI
Download and install the Heroku CLI.

If you haven't already, log in to your Heroku account and follow the prompts to create a new SSH public key.

$ heroku login
Clone the repository
Use Git to clone open-back-chat's source code to your local machine.

$ heroku git:clone -a open-back-chat
$ cd open-back-chat
Deploy your changes
Make some changes to the code you just cloned and deploy them to Heroku using Git.

$ git add .
$ git commit -am "make it better"
$ git push heroku master

